            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EGuilt%20does%20not%20simply%20go%20away.%20The%20modern%20method%20of%20denying%20guilt%20just%20postpones%20it%20until%20a%20later%20day.%20Repressed%20and%20denied%20guilt%20will%20always%20resurface%20in%20the%20form%20of%20anger%2C%20bitterness%2C%20rejection%2C%20and%20failure.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGod%20knows%20how%20unforgiven%20sin%20will%20destroy%20you%20and%20your%20relationship%20with%20Him%20and%20others.%20In%20the%20Old%20Testament%2C%20He%20gave%20instructions%20for%20the%20guilt%20offering%20that%20related%20to%20any%20situation%2C%20whether%20it%20was%20the%20high%20priest%2C%20a%20leader%2C%20an%20individual%2C%20or%20the%20entire%20community%20that%20had%20sinned.%20The%20only%20way%20to%20be%20forgiven%20in%20the%20Old%20Testament%20system%20was%20to%20bring%20an%20individual%20sacrifice.%20Worshipers%20brought%20a%20bull%2C%20a%20goat%2C%20a%20lamb%2C%20two%20pigeons%2C%20or%20a%20handful%20of%20fine%20flour%2C%20depending%20upon%20their%20status%20and%20means.%20No%20sin%20or%20negligence%20was%20swept%20under%20the%20rug%20by%20God%20but%20was%20paid%20for%20by%20something.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESinners%20are%20Jesus'%20specialty.%20The%20Bible%20tells%20us%20that%20not%20only%20is%20God%20precise%20with%20sin%2C%20but%20He%20is%20also%20merciful%20toward%20sinners.%20Take%20Levi%2C%20for%20example.%20Jesus%20accepted%20Levi's%20invitation%20to%20dine%20with%20him%20and%20his%20friends%2C%20who%20were%20notorious%20sinners.%20When%20the%20Pharisees%20discovered%20this%2C%20they%20criticized%20the%20Lord.%20Jesus%20responded%2C%20%22I%20have%20come%20to%20call%20sinners%2C%20not%20those%20who%20think%20they%20are%20already%20good%20enough%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E(Mark%202%3A17).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJesus%20is%20your%20%22guilt%20offering.%22%20Release%20your%20guilt%20to%20the%20cross%20and%20praise%20Him%2C%20knowing%20that%20you%20were%20once%20a%20sinner%20but%20now%20have%20been%20forgiven.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
